ects are not uniform across nations. Bringing together a range of expert contributions, the key lesson to emerge from this book is that 'the crisis' is better understood as a variety of crises, each mediated by national context. Consequently, there is an array of potential trajectories for welfare systems, from those where social policy is regarded as incompatible with the post-crisis economy to those where it is considered essential to future economic growth and security.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEconomic policy. 0aSocial policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh1 aBarrientos, Armando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBéland, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConsidine, Mairéad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCook, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeacon, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDukelow, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarnsworth, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarnsworth, Kevin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGough, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHudson, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrving, Zoë, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIrving, Zoë, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKosonen, Pekka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKühner, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c